page 98-107
1. ip link => show the network devices and their status
ip link set dev <devname> up/down
2. ip a    => show the network devices ip addresses
3. ip a add <ip> dev <devicename> => to add a new ip to your device
4. ip r => to show rout table, route => to show route table 
ip r add <cidr> via <router ip> 
5. traceroute <host> => shows all hops to the destination host
6. telnet <host> <port> => to test connectivity to a specific port on a specific host 
7. ss ( successor netstat ) => to show listening serices in a host
ss -l for listen, -t for tcp, -u for udp, -n for number, -p for process 


Steps: 
1. ip link
2. nslookup 
3. traceroute
4. ss



Docker commands
1. docker run <image>
2. docker run <image> <command>
3. docker run -i <image> <command> => interactive mode
4. docker run -it <image> command> => interactive terminal
5. docker run -p <hostport>:<containerport> <image>
